{"id":"287259184_Advances_in_self-healing_ceramic_matrix_composites","abstract":"Self-healing is the capacity of a system to repair damage by itself so that cracks are sealed. For ceramic materials, especially ceramic matrix composites (CMCs), cracks can exist after processing or are created by a mechanical or thermal load. At high temperature in a moist oxidizing environment, cracks allow oxygen diffusion inside the bulk, provoking chemical degradation. To limit oxygen progression, an oxide glassy phase is used to fill cracks. This oxide is added as a protective coating or is formed by oxidation of non-oxide compounds in a protective coating or in the bulk. In the latter, the constituent undergoing oxidation acts as a chemical fuse against oxidation. Self-healing remains efficient if the oxide is chemically and thermally stable.","authors":["F. Rebillat"],"meta":["February 2014","DOI:10.1533/9780857098825.2.369"],"references":["297866619_Thermal_Expansion_and_Oxidation_of_3D_CSiC_Composites_with_Different_Coatings_from_Room_Temperature_to_1400C","263601829_Paralinear_Oxidation_of_SiC_in_Water_Vapor","229917313_Oxidation_and_Volatilization_of_Silica_Formers_in_Water_Vapor","229593878_High-Temperature_Oxidation_of_Boron_Nitride_I_Monolithic_Boron_Nitride","229200254_TEM_structure_of_PyCSiCn_multilayered_interphases_in_SiCSiC_composites","289874810_Ceramic_gas_turbine_development_at_Solar_Turbines_Incorporated","288122234_Overview_on_the_Self-Sealing_Process_in_the_SiC_F_SICB_M_Composites_under_Wet_Atmosphere_at_High_Temperature","285490802_Processing_and_characterization_of_3D_carbon_fiber_reinforced_silicon_carbide_and_silicon_nitride_matrix_composites","285468593_Interphases_in_ceramic_matrix_composites","284739730_Etude_cinetique_de_l'oxydation_du_graphite_inhibee_par_les_phosphates","265301282_General_Relationship_for_the_Thermal_Oxidation_of_Silicon","263314063_Oxidation-based_materials_selection_for_2000C_hypersonic_aerosurfaces_Theoretical_considerations_and_h